    category: "TREK_ROUTE",
    summary: `The Rolwaling Valley is a sacred glacial wilderness tucked into the mountains of Dolakha, sheltering the high-altitude settlements of Beding and Na beneath the peak of Gauri Shankar. The spectacular Tashi Lapcha Pass (5,755m) connects this hidden valley to the Everest region in a crossing that is as technically demanding as it is scenically overwhelming.`,
    story: `<p>Rolwaling, whose name translates roughly as 'the furrow left by a plough', is one of Nepal's most remote inhabited valleys, a glacial trough enclosed by peaks of extraordinary beauty and largely inaccessible except on foot. The valley is sacred to Nyingma Buddhists, who regard it as one of Nepal's beyul or hidden valleys, places of spiritual refuge concealed by Guru Rinpoche for a future time of need. The sense of sanctuary is still palpable in the clean air, the absence of noise and the unhurried pace of life in the villages of Beding and Na.</p><p>The trek begins from Simigaon or Dolakha Bazaar in Dolakha District, climbing through terraced farmland and rhododendron forest before entering the upper valley proper. Beding at 3,690 metres is the last sizeable settlement, a cluster of stone houses and a working gompa surrounded by meadows that become snowfield in winter. Higher up, the grazing settlement of Na at 4,183 metres is the last habitation before the glacier begins.</p><p>The centrepiece and climax of the full Rolwaling experience is the crossing of Tashi Lapcha Pass at 5,755 metres, a glaciated col that requires crampons, ice axes and ropes on the ascent, and connects the valley to the Khumbu region near Thame. This is not a trekking pass in the conventional sense but a genuine mountaineering objective, requiring prior technical experience and ideally a qualified guide with glacier training.</p><p>Tsho Rolpa, the glacial lake at the head of the valley, has become famous in climate discussions as one of the most rapidly expanding glacial lakes in Nepal. Trekkers visiting this melancholy but beautiful body of water are witnessing climate change in one of its most direct and visible expressions. The Rolwaling Valley rewards those willing to earn its rewards with memories that endure long after the trail dust washes away.</p>`,
    district: `Dolakha`,
    province: "BAGMATI",
    lat: 27.8833,
    lng: 86.4333,
    elevation: 5755,
    entryFee: `Gaurishankar Conservation Area NPR 2000; TIMS card required`,
    bestSeason: `Oct-Nov, Mar-May`,
    openingHours: `Always open`,
    howToGetThere: `Drive from Kathmandu to Charikot or Simigaon (5-7 hrs). Trek begins from Simigaon or Nyimare. If crossing Tashi Lapcha Pass, exit at Thame and descend to Namche Bazaar then fly home from Lukla. Technical gear required for the pass.`,
    trekDays: 17,
